  "body": "\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: On sender side transaction message shows \"Pending\" for transaction sent in 1:1 chat 20 minutes ago. Transaction has more than 100 confirmations.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nIf transaction is confirmed then send transaction message in 1:1 chat shows state \"Confirmed\" for both sender and receiver. \r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nOn sender side send transaction message shows \"Pending\" state\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open 1:1 chat on iOs and Android devices\r\n- as iOS device: send to Android 0.0001 ETH\r\n- wait ~5 minutes and do not navigate anywhere else on both devices, so 1:1 chats are open. In my case, on Android side transaction will be shown as Confirmed soon. \r\n- as soon as tx is Confirmed on Android: do not touch iOS and do not do anything else there. On Android you can navigate to Wallet -> transaction history to make sure tx has enough confirmations. As soon as there are more than 12 - look in 1:1 chat on iOS.\r\n\r\nSee from 2:22:12 start and send transaction message test. https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/8500343/sessions/4394438169/?accessToken=ydDyz4laS11IuKUE/CP/K50FKNA\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: nightly build June 20\r\n[comment]: # (Android or iOS.)\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/8500343/sessions/4394438169/?accessToken=ydDyz4laS11IuKUE/CP/K50FKNA\">TestFairy: Status 0.9.21 (6078) @2018</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
